$ System.BitConverter (class)

`System.BitConverter` allows to convert base types to byte → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Array[arrays] and vice versa.

The method `GetBytes(val)` is overloaded for various base types and returns the base type's internal byte representation with which it stores `val`
-
The methods `ToX(byteArray)` convert `byteArray` to the base type `X` (for example `ToInt32()`).

{ PowerShell example

  The following → Windows/PowerShell example converts an → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Int32[`Int32`] to a
  → Windows/PowerShell/language/type/array/byte[byte array]:
  gh|.NET-API|/System/BitConverter/X-to-bytes.ps1||

}

sa:
  The → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Convert/index#System-Convert-To[`ToX` methods in `System.Convert`] that convert
  certain values to → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/_integral-numeric-types[intergral numeric types].

